table asyncio_extra166.asyncio_name_length_cross_comparison:
  description: "asyncio.Handle, Future, Task class name and module length cross-comparison in asyncionlc166 namespace — asyncio.Handle.__name__.__len__()==6 ('Handle'=6: 'H'+'a'+'n'+'d'+'l'+'e'=6; same as Future.__name__.__len__()==6 — Handle and Future share the same 6-char class name length; Task is shorter at 4); asyncio.Handle.__module__.__len__()==14 ('asyncio.events'=14: 'asyncio'=7+'.'=1+'events'=6=14; Handle module len(14) > Future module len(8) by 6 because Handle is pure Python in asyncio.events while Future is C-accelerated in _asyncio); asyncio.Future.__name__.__len__()==6 (cross-check; Future(6)==Handle(6) in name length; both 6-char class names); asyncio.Task.__name__.__len__()==4 (Task(4) < Future(6)==Handle(6); Task has the shortest name: 'Task'=4 vs 'Future'=6 vs 'Handle'=6; Task(4) is 2 chars shorter than Future and Handle); KEY PATTERN: Future==Handle(6 chars) > Task(4 chars) in class name length; '_asyncio'(8) < 'asyncio.events'(14) in module name length — C modules vs Python modules; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
